<p>I grep for a word/pattern in a file, if such a pattern doesn't exist in a file, then I want to print/echo "-". Can we do this on command line in a single lined command?</p>  <pre><code>grep word &lt;file&gt; | &lt;command to return "-" if "word" not present in file&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>Similarly if script returns nothing , echo "-"</p>  <pre><code>python script.py | &lt;command to return "-" if script returns nothing/NULL </code></pre>